{"id":"2010.02184","submitter":"Leon Sering","authors":"Leon Sering","title":"Multi-Commodity Nash Flows Over Time","comments":"Version sent to MOR","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cs.GT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Motivated by the dynamic traffic assignment problem, we consider flows over\ntime model with deterministic queuing. Dynamic equilibria, called Nash flows\nover time, have been studied intensively since their introduction by Koch and\nSkutella in 2009. Unfortunately, the original model can only handle a single\ncommodity, i.e., all flow goes from one origin to one destination, therefore,\nthis theory is not applicable to every-day traffic scenarios. For this reason\nwe consider Nash flows over time in a setting with multiple commodities, each\nwith a individual origin and destination. We prove their existence with the\nhelp of multi-commodity thin flows with resetting. This proof gives some\ninteresting structural insights into the strategy profiles underlying the\nequilibria, as they emphasis the inter-commodity dependencies. Finally, we show\nthat the two special cases of a common origin or a common destination can be\nreduced to the single-commodity case.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Oct 2020 17:44:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-06"}
