etric accuracy of 0.11 mas. To confidently detect binaries\nwith $M_c>10^{7}~M_\\odot$ out to 50 Mpc, a factor of 100 sensitivity\nimprovement is required. We propose several improvement strategies, including\nrecovering the mean astrometric deflection and increasing astrometric accuracy,\nnumber of observed stars, field-of-view size, and observational cadence. We\ndiscuss how other existing and planned photometric surveys could contribute to\ndetecting GWs via astrometry.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Oct 2020 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 16 Mar 2021 08:08:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-13"}
