assive companions (e.g. ~70 per cent merge over timescales of ~3.5 Gyrs), with\nthe dark-matter-deficient population being constantly replenished by new\ninteractions between dwarfs and massive companions. The creation of these\ngalaxies is, therefore, a natural by-product of galaxy evolution and their\nexistence is not in tension with the standard paradigm.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Oct 2020 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 7 Jan 2021 23:49:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-20"}
